<doc id="1274161" wikidata="Q8075904" url="?curid=1274161" title="Zygovisti">
<text>Zygovisti (, also Ζιγοβίστι &quot;Zigovisti&quot;) is a village in the municipal unit Dimitsana, western Arcadia, Greece. It is located in the mountains east of the river Lousios, 3 km southeast of Dimitsana and 4 km north of Stemnitsa. At 1160 m elevation, it is one of the highest villages in Greece. There is a large marble book in the village square, commemorating the Greek War of Independence. It is considered a traditional settlement.

==Historical population==
